# Data architecture

## Principle

Keep **repeatable content** out of page files. Use typed modules under `src/data/` and import into pages, sections, and components.

## Recommended data modules (extend as needed)

| File (example)        | Purpose |
|----------------------|---------|
| `demos.ts`           | Homepage demo definitions, slugs, section order |
| `navigation.ts`      | Main nav, footer links |
| `footer-links.ts`    | Footer columns (when split from nav) |
| `features.ts`        | Feature lists / grids |
| `pricing.ts`         | Tiers, copy |
| `testimonials.ts`    | Quotes, avatars |
| `faq.ts`             | Questions / answers |
| `integrations.ts`    | Integration logos, links |
| `use-cases.ts`       | Use case cards |
| `customers.ts`       | Logos / stories |
| `blog.ts`            | Post metadata (or move to CMS later) |
| `careers.ts`         | Job listings |
| `prompts.ts`         | In-app prompt library demo data |
| `workflows.ts`       | Workflow automation demo |
| `analytics.ts`       | Dashboard chart / KPI demo |
| `dashboard-nav.ts`   | Sidebar / app nav |

## Routes

- Central paths live in **`src/routes.ts`**. When adding a page, **add the path** there first, then use `routes.*` in components and data (avoid stringly-typed URLs).
- Route groups **do not** appear in the URL: `(marketing)/pricing/page.tsx` → `/pricing`.

## Demo system

- Multiple home demos should be driven from **`demos.ts`** (slug, title, `sectionOrder`, `heroVariant`) — not unrelated one-off pages.
